text: The total number of international tourist arrivals to Sri Lanka during August 2019 was 143,587. In comparison to
August last year, there was a decline of 28.3% when the arrivals were 200,359.
This month, the largest source market for tourists was India, followed by the United Kingdom and China.
Almost 99 % of tourists travelled by air to Sri Lanka.
As at 31st August 2019, 1,267,737 of tourists had visited Sri Lanka for this year. It is a decline of 19.9% over last
year when 1,582,835 of tourists has visited the country during the same period.
Europe became the largest source of tourist traffic to Sri Lanka with 38% of the total traffic received in August 2019.
Asia and Pacific accounted for 51% of the total traffic, America 6%, Middle East 4% and Africa 1%.

TOP TEN SOURCE MARKETS India, United Kingdom, China, Germany and France were Sri Lanka’s top five international tourist generating markets in the month of August this year. India was the largest source of tourist traffic to Sri Lanka with 26% of the total traffic received in August 2019. UK accounted for 10% of the total traffic; while China, Germany and France accounted for 7% and 5% (both) respectively.
